    "abstract": "Following the recent work of (Doerner et al., CCS 2025), we introduce an improved reduction of OLE to OT. We prove the following: there is a perfectly-secure OLE-to-OT reduction over any $n$-bit field $\\mathbb{F}$ using almost-linear communication $n\\cdot 2^{O(\\log^{*} n)}$ and almost-constant rounds $O((\\log^{*} n)^2)$. In the course of proving our result, we also introduce new perfectly-secure protocols for computing shares of the equality and greater-than predicate on $n$-bit strings in the OT-hybrid model using $O(n)$ communication and $\\log^{*} n$ rounds. These results are of independent interest.",
